.TH CONFLUEX 1 "May 2026" "confluex 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
confluex \- export Confluence page scopes to Markdown
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B confluex setup
.br
.B confluex export --page-id
.I id
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B confluex
is a token-authenticated command line tool for exporting Confluence page scopes
to Markdown and operator reports.
.PP
Use
.B setup
to save reusable Confluence access settings. Use
.B export
to inspect a page scope, materialize Markdown payloads, retain attachments, and
write reports. Add
.B --plan-only
to inspect scope and reports without materializing page payloads.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B setup
Interactively save the Confluence base URL and token in the user configuration
file. The token prompt does not echo input.
.TP
.B export
Validate root-page access, discover the selected page scope, and write the
governed report set. By default this command also writes Markdown page payloads
and retained attachments.
.SH EXPORT MODES
.TP
.B materialized
Default mode. Writes reports, Markdown page payloads, and retained attachments
under the selected output root. This mode supports
.BR --zip
and
.BR --resume .
.TP
.B plan_only
Selected by
.BR --plan-only .
Writes reports for the selected scope without materializing page payloads or
attachments. This mode does not imply any other option.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Required selection
.TP
.BI --page-id " id"
Root Confluence page id to export or inspect.
.SS Output and mode
.TP
.BI --out " path"
Output directory. If omitted, Confluex generates one in the current directory.
.TP
.B --plan-only
Inspect export scope and reports without materializing page payloads.
.TP
.B --debug
Write sanitized diagnostic artifacts inside
.I _debug/
under the selected output root. Debug artifacts include run metadata, effective
options, events, page metadata, storage XML, attachment-preview data, and
markdown-exporter diagnostics for operations that were actually performed.
.TP
.B --zip
Create a ZIP archive beside the Markdown output root.
.TP
.B --resume
Reuse a compatible incomplete materialized export root selected by
.BR --out .
.SS Scope control
.TP
.B --include-children
Include the recursive Confluence child tree of the root page. If omitted,
Confluex does not traverse child pages.
.TP
.BI --link-depth " n"
Follow supported internal links up to
.I n
hops from pages already in scope. The default is 1.
.TP
.BI --max-find-candidates " n"
Inspect at most
.I n
title-resolution candidates per link.
.SS Safety limits
.TP
.BI --max-pages " n"
Stop after
.I n
processed pages.
.TP
.BI --max-download-mib " n"
Stop after downloading
.I n
MiB in total.
.SS Runtime behavior
.TP
.B --no-fail-fast
Continue after page-local runtime failures.
.TP
.BI --sleep-ms " n"
Sleep
.I n
milliseconds between processed pages.
.SS Configuration input
.TP
.BI --env-file " file"
Load public configuration from an explicit env file.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration precedence is command-line options, explicit env file, default
current-directory
.IR .confluex.env ,
user config written by
.BR setup ,
process environment, then no value.
.PP
Supported public configuration names are
.BR CONFLUEX_CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL ,
.BR CONFLUEX_CONFLUENCE_TOKEN ,
.BR CONFLUEX_OUTPUT_ROOT ,
.BR CONFLUEX_MAX_PAGES ,
.BR CONFLUEX_MAX_DOWNLOAD_MIB ,
.BR CONFLUEX_SLEEP_MS ,
.BR CONFLUEX_MAX_FIND_CANDIDATES ,
and
.BR CONFLUEX_LINK_DEPTH .
.PP
Tokens are used as Bearer token values for Confluence requests. Confluex does
not print token values in setup prompts, command output, reports, or debug
artifacts.
.SH OUTPUTS
.TP
.I summary.txt
Run outcome summary. It includes
.B command=export
and
.B execution_mode
for the selected export mode.
.TP
.I manifest.tsv
Selected page inventory, including page id, space key, title, output folder,
discovery source, execution mode, and attachment count.
.TP
.I resolved-links.tsv
Supported links resolved into the selected scope.
.TP
.I unresolved-links.tsv
Supported links that could not be resolved into the selected scope.
.TP
.I failed-pages.tsv
Page-local failures.
.TP
.I scope-findings.tsv
Scope and discovery findings.
.TP
.I pages/
Materialized Markdown page payloads and retained attachments.
.TP
.I _debug/
Sanitized diagnostic artifacts written only when
.B --debug
is supplied.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success, success with findings, or help.
.TP
.B 1
Rejected invocation or setup validation failure.
.TP
.B 3
Configured stop condition.
.TP
.B 4
Runtime failure.
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by signal.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/confluex/config.json
User config on Linux and XDG environments when
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is set.
.TP
.I $HOME/.config/confluex/config.json
User config on Linux and XDG environments when
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is not set.
.TP
.I %APPDATA%\econfluex\econfig.json
User config on Windows.
.TP
.I ./.confluex.env
Default current-directory env file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Configure reusable access:
.B confluex setup
.TP
Validate access and inspect the planned scope:
.B confluex export --page-id 12345 --plan-only --out ./plan
.TP
Export Markdown and create a ZIP archive:
.B confluex export --page-id 12345 --out ./dump --zip
.TP
Export with diagnostic artifacts:
.B confluex export --page-id 12345 --out ./dump --debug
.TP
Resume an incomplete materialized export:
.B confluex export --page-id 12345 --out ./dump --resume
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR npm (1)
